NTFS read-only access!!! Let me say that again: You may not need this plug-in for average USB access on your phone, but it's fantastic - and safe - for read-only NTFS access from whichever phone you're using - mine's a Note 4. I've had, let's say a little trouble, with Paragon's solution if write is enabled (@$&!) - so why bother with that, even for read only, when SE can handle reading effortlessly and natively? So yes, buy and use this plug-in! Works great on SSDs or self-powered spinning drives I haven't tested it on a really huge one - 1gb worked fine - but I see no reason it wouldn't work. Gives you access to massive amounts of data on the go. And yes, I want to keep my NTFS formatting (over exFAT) for reasons beyond the scope of this review. This is yet another almost hidden amazing feature from SE - such as their incredibly powerful bulk renaming.

It works, but it's appallingly slow. I tested two transfer methods, (both in Solid Explorer) one allowing SE to mount/control the OTG drive, the other simply allowing Android to mount it in the usual location (/mnt/media_rw/<USB_ID>/) and using root access to copy to that folder.   Using this plugin (and allowing SE to manage the OTG drive) I got a maximum of 80KB/s, and it stayed at that speed very steadily the whole time, almost seemed intentionally throttled.  Using the Android mount with root method, I got anywhere from 4MB/s to around 12MB/s. For anyone too lazy to do the math, that's over 50 times faster at only the LOWEST SPEED. Over 100 times faster at it's higher speeds.  Put simply, this plugin is UNUSABLE for anything more than the occasional song transfer. (All testing was done on Android 6.0.1 with a Nexus 6 [shamu])
